  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT344-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">piriviṭai vaṟpuṟuttun tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ kūriyatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken by HER to the confidante who encourages [her] in
          the time of separation. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT344">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> nōṟṟōr maṉṟa tōḻi taṇṇeṉat</l>
          <l> tūṟṟun tuvalaip paṉikkaṭun tiṅkaṭ</l>
          <l> pulampayi rarunta vaṇṇa lēṟoṭu</l>
          <l> nilantūṅ kaṇala vīṅkumulaic ceruttal</l>
          <l> pālvār kuḻavi yuḷḷi niraiyiṟan</l>
          <l> tūrvayiṟ peyarum puṉkaṇ mālai</l>
          <l> yarumpeṟaṟ poruṭpiṇip pōkip</l>
          <l> pirintuṟai kātalar varakkāṇ pōrē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Penance have they done indeed, friend,</l>
          <l>who see the long -separated lover coming,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">having gone enticed by wealth difficult to obtain,</l>
          <l rend="indent">at sorrowful evening, when those with dewlaps </l>
          <l rend="indent8">hanging to the ground,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">traversing the row in remembrance of [their] calves,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">milk flowing over from udders with swelling teats,</l>
          <l rend="indent">are returning to the village</l>
          <l rend="indent2">with [their] majestic bull, as they eat of the corn from the fields,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">in the month of heavy dew with drops spreading coolly.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
